      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Space.com, a New York multimedia company that bundles astronomy-related content, eliminated 22 jobs, or about 22 percent of its work force, on Friday as a part of a plan to make the company profitable next year.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Space.com, a New York multimedia company that bundles astronomy-related content, eliminated 22 jobs, or about 22 percent of its work force, on Friday as a part of a plan to make the company profitable next year.</p>
        <p>The layoffs come three days after the resignation of Space.com's president, Sally Ride, the first American woman in space, who said she wanted to focus on science education.</p>
        <p>Jayson Blair (NYT)</p>
      </block>
